dc_description_s: A plan of the operations of the King's army under the command of General Sr. William Howe, K.B. in New York and east New Jersey, against the American forces commanded by General Washington, from the 12th of October, to the 28th of November 1776. Wherein is particularly distinguished the engagement on the White Plains, the 28th of October
